Listen to this podcast. You'll know that nanopass founder @reicannon is someone who knows what he is doing. He is certainly not just vibin and goofing around.

You need a TEAM. 

And that's why I'm so bullish with @nanoverseHQ. They have like 15 core team members across different industries. Devs, artists, streamers & gamers, designer, businessman, analyst, marketing specialist, lawyers, CPA, and so on.

And the expectations are high once you do raise those amount of funds. 

I'm also not that bullish on projects that are too much reliant on one person, whether it's the artist, the dev or the founder. Again, an NFT project is like a business, you need a competent team to run it.

Nothing against very young founders. Some of them are still in high school, it's cool and all but they still lack relevant life, business & managerial experience. Passion for a project alone won't be enough. Raising several million USD is a lot of responsibility.

Running an NFT project is like running a business and a brand...it's not just about passion, art, vibe, and so on. 

Execution is super important and it helps a lot if you have experience.
